  {
    "id": 51,
    "title": "Carl Theodor Reiffenstein",
    "type": "classic",
    "subtitle": "A Frankfurt artist explores the old town",
    "description": "",
    "prologue": "",
    "steps": [
      {
        "id": 387,
        "location": {
          "type": "Point",
          "coordinates": [
            8.682594070786337,
            50.10959403062543
          ]
        },
        "title": "A Frankfurt artist explores the old town",
        "type": "start",
        "splitPosition": "split",
        "splitAnchor": 1.02,
        "turnByTurn": 1,
        "textContents": [
          {
            "pos": 3,
            "template": "plain",
            "body": "<p>Explore Frankfurt’s 19th-cen­tury Old Town with local landscape artist Carl Theodor Reiffenstein (1820-1893)!</p>\n<p>Born in Grau­ben­gasse lane (today the Kleinmarkthalle), Reiffenstein grew up in the heart of the Old Town. Every free hour he had, he spent sketching sce­nes in his home town and surroundings. He found his main motifs not just in the Old Town’s buildings, streets and squa­res, but also in the city walls, courtyards and gar­dens.</p>\n<p>In 2,000 water­co­lours and drawings and over 2,400 manu­script pages, he captured his impres­si­ons of 19th-cen­tury Frankfurt. Usually he drew the sce­nes on site in pencil, later turning his drawings into water­co­lour sket­ches. His extensive wri­tings describe pla­ces and details of architectu­ral his­tory, as well as recor­ding his­to­rical events and anec­do­tes.</p>\n<p>Many pla­ces Reiffenstein documented no lon­ger exist; just a few have survived unch­anged or were recon­structed.</p>",
            "metadata": {
              "title": "",
              "description": "",
              "accessibleDescription": "",
              "author": "Carina Koch",
              "copyright": null,
              "ticketLink": null,
              "contentType": "App\\Models\\TextContent",
              "expires": null
            },
            "filters": []
          }
